          <h3>What happens in winter when solar isn't enough?</h3>
          <p>
            There will be two to four months of the year, typically June through August, where your solar production drops below what you need to cover your usage and fully charge the battery. This is normal.
          </p>
          <p>
            That's where the right electricity plan matters most. We can set your system to force charge the battery from the grid during off peak hours or during free periods like Glowbird's 11am to 2pm window. Your battery still gets full, your home still runs off stored energy in the evening, and you're still paying far less than a standard electricity plan.
          </p>
          <p>
            We build this winter strategy into every VPP setup. It's not an afterthought.
          </p>
